<title>CANADA: Brookfield plans C$400 millon share offer.</title>
<headline>Brookfield plans C$400 millon share offer.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1997-07-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brookfield Properties Corp said on Thursday it agreed to sell 21,052,632 common shares to an investment dealer group led by CIBC Wood Gundy Securities Inc for C$19 a share in a C$400 million offering.</p>
<p>The company said proceeds would be used to fund pending acquisitions and repay debt.</p>
<p>It said EdperBrascan Corp agreed to purchase 10.5 million shares for total proceeds of $200 million. The deal would give EdperBrascan about a 52 stake in Brookfield on a fully diluted basis.</p>
<p>((Reuters Toronto Bureau 416-941-8100))</p>
